    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for various members of the order Lepidoptera, typically those distinguished from butterflies by being nocturnal and having less colorful wings. Since moths are not a monophyletic group, they cannot be placed together in a scientific taxon.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
